n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/qrs-complex-abnormalities-in-cardiac-health\/\">QRS complex abnormalities: Clarifying ECG Abnormalities for Heart Health<\/a><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4a0bb83 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"4a0bb83\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Related Article Understanding t wave abnormalities symptoms causes and treatment P wave ecg abnormalities and their role in cardiac wellness QRS complex abnormalities: Clarifying ECG Abnormalities for Heart Health Author:- Mr. Ritesh Sharma As you must already know, when it comes to cardiac care, an electrocardiogram is one of the most essential tests. While in [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2270,"featured_media":37710,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"content-type":"","footnotes":""},"categories":[113],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-37643","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-heart-health-tips"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/37643"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2270"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=37643"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/37643\/revisions"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/37710"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-json\/w